    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nFinish the program so the `Painter` reaches the traffic cone.\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/c7c7276f9f01ead2a807d8cbe22b71d6-Animation.gif)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nTo create a `Painter` and move forward one space, use\r\n\r\n   ```\r\n   painter_name = Painter()\r\n   painter_name.move()\r\n   ```\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n\r\n   ```\r\n   1  alicia = Painter()\r\n   2  alicia.move()\r\n   ```\r\n\r\nIn this example, `alicia = Painter()` creates the `Painter`, and `alicia.move()` moves the `Painter` forward one space.\r\n\r\n<br/>\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-hand-back-point-right\"></i> **By the way!** Click the book icon above the workspace to learn more about the `Painter` object and `move()` method in the Python documentation.\r\n",
